HEADWORD: Unijugate
<hw>U*nij"u*gate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets>
+ L. <ets>jugum</ets> yoke, pair: cf. L. <ets>unijugus</ets> having one
yoke.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having but one pair of leaflets; --
said of a pinnate leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

